column5: Here's a picture form 3 different lake s and trips from 2006-2009
Great photos of those pike - thanks for sharing ! Our annual May Ontario trip isn't far away, and I'm counting down the days ! Rich B

I have really enjoyed letting my mind wonder, checking out these great pics and vids here my trip Osullivans Rainbow last few days of June first few of July More vids on the bloghttp://walleyewarrior.blogspot.com/

Great vids ER620. You do a fantastic job of capturing it all so others can see. I've been to O'Sullivan many times and going back this year at the end of July. It was fun looking at all your pics and figuring out where you were fishing. Bob and Shelly have made great improvements in recent years. Looking forward to getting back there this year. Great looking fishing machine you've got there too.
shore lunch
Bob and Shelly are the best, they even "handled" all the flying critters for us last year, as we ate dinner outside in peace! Can't wait to return!
When were you at South Bay??
Morning launch, a nice smallmouth, and the camp at sunset.It's going to be a good year.NimstugIce out in ~7 weeks.

5 months from today we will be sitting in a boat on Kayedon lake out of Nakina. My three boys and I So u r not alone. !!!!!
I've enjoyed the pics all. Keep 'em coming. 5 months and 8 days til Twin Lakes near Nakina and 5 months and 15 days to O'Sullivan Lake NW of Nakina. Can't wait to get back.
Trip to Wettlaufer Lake July 2009. The handsome guy is fishfearme holding up the 29" walleye and the 39 1/2" pike
I love those Caramel Colored Sunsets in the north country. July 29th can not get here soon enough. Long awaited and needed fly-in for wallies and smallies!!!!!!!!!!
I think Lake of the Woods has earned it's reputation as the Sunset Country. Here are a couple from Sabaskong Bay I think you will like.
Wow!!!!You guys are great. Thanks for some fantastic pictures and responses to this thread. Keep those pics flowing. The soft water season is coming fast!Scott

I'm getting walleye cabin fever. Our trip to Lac Seul is not until July. I'm hoping some of you can post some pictures of pretty Canadian scenes, fish, folks, and fun to wet the appetite. Let's start dreaming. Show us your pics!

We enjoy the scenery as much as the fishing. Here are a few of my favorites.Links to moose and rabbit videos are:Moose+Calf -- http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wSeDL2j_6FwBunny in Boat -- http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wOs96l6NALEWallerChief -- great videos, man!!
Chapleau camping trip August 2010
Attawapiskat River June 2010. Walleyes were incredibly aggressive, and mostly incidental catches while casting for pike.
That waterfall wouldn't be at the end of South Inlet would it?Looks like it was flowing pretty well?

Saluki - Couple of great videos Especially the moose cow/calf. We have had moose swim across in front of us on a couple of trips.gibby: When you see the "night danger" signs - it's for real - if you're going to drive at night, you definitely need to be watching for them.

tv4fish: Couldn't agree with you more about driving danger at night! Went bumper to knees with a young moose once and it scared the "BeJesus" out of everyone in the vehicle. Was on 502 heading north and, after topping a hill, saw a young moose in the middle of the road. Hit the brakes hard and barely got stopped in time. Didn't bother it though ... it casually walked off to the side of the road.
